# GoalifyNow E2E Testing Best Practices

## Overview
This document provides guidelines for creating and maintaining E2E tests using Playwright for the GoalifyNow application.

## Test Structure

### Directory Organization
```
tests/
├── config/           # Test configuration
│   ├── test-config.ts
│   └── playwright.config.ts
├── fixtures/         # Test data fixtures
├── pages/            # Page Object Models
├── specs/            # Test specifications
│   ├── smoke/        # Critical path tests
│   ├── properties/   # Property management tests
│   ├── rentals/      # Rental management tests
│   ├── tenants/      # Tenant management tests
│   ├── inventories/  # Inventory tests
│   ├── floor-plans/  # Floor plan tests
│   ├── inspections/  # Inspection tests
│   └── billing/      # Billing tests
├── setup/            # Test fixtures and setup
└── utils/            # Helper utilities
```

### Page Object Model (POM) Pattern
Always use Page Object Models for interacting with UI elements:

```typescript
// pages/example-page.ts
import { Page, Locator, expect } from '@playwright/test';
import { BasePage } from './base-page';
import TestConfig from '../config/test-config';

export class ExamplePage extends BasePage {
  // Use data-testid attributes when available
  readonly pageTitle = '[data-testid="page-title"]';
  readonly submitButton = '[data-testid="submit-button"]';
  
  // Fallback to text-based selectors
  readonly createButton = 'button:has-text("Create")';
  
  constructor(page: Page) {
    super(page);
  }

  async goto(): Promise<void> {
    await this.page.goto('/example');
    await this.waitForPageLoad();
  }

  async verifyPageDisplayed(): Promise<void> {
    await expect(this.page.locator(this.pageTitle)).toBeVisible();
  }
}
```

## Test Tags and Categorization

### Required Tags
All tests MUST use appropriate tags for CI/CD categorization:

- `@smoke` - Critical path tests that should run on every deployment
- `@regression` - Full regression tests for CI pipelines
- `@prod` - Tests safe to run on production (read-only)
- `@local` - Tests that create/modify data (local/staging only)

### Feature-Specific Tags
- `@properties` - Property management tests
- `@rentals` - Rental management tests
- `@tenants` - Tenant management tests
- `@inventories` - Inventory tests
- `@floorplans` - Floor plan tests
- `@inspections` - Inspection tests
- `@billing` - Billing tests

### Example Tag Usage
```typescript
test.describe('Feature Page @feature @regression', () => {
  test.describe('Page Display @smoke @prod', () => {
    test('should display page correctly', async () => {
      // Test implementation
    });
  });

  test.describe('Data Modification @regression @local', () => {
    test('should create new item', async () => {
      // Test implementation
    });
  });
});
```

## Test Guidelines

### 1. Authentication
- Use seeded demo users for authentication
- Login via `LoginPage.login()` method
- Wait for login completion before proceeding

```typescript
test.beforeEach(async ({ page, demoUsersAvailable }) => {
  test.skip(!demoUsersAvailable, 'Demo users not seeded - skipping test');
  
  const loginPage = new LoginPage(page);
  await loginPage.goto();
  await loginPage.login(
    TestConfig.credentials.landlord.email,
    TestConfig.credentials.landlord.password
  );
  
  await page.waitForURL(url => !url.pathname.includes('/auth/login'), { timeout: 30000 });
});
```

### 2. Selectors Priority
1. `data-testid` attributes (most reliable)
2. ARIA labels and roles
3. Text-based selectors
4. CSS class selectors (least preferred)

### 3. Wait Strategies
- Use `waitForSelector` instead of arbitrary timeouts
- Use `Promise.race` for multiple possible outcomes
- Use `waitForURL` for navigation completion

```typescript
// Good: Wait for specific conditions
await Promise.race([
  this.page.waitForSelector('[data-testid="data-table"]', { state: 'visible' }),
  this.page.waitForSelector('[data-testid="empty-state"]', { state: 'visible' })
]);

// Avoid: Arbitrary timeouts
await page.waitForTimeout(5000);  // Don't do this
```

### 4. Test Data Management
- Use seeded E2E test users
- Clean up test data after modifications
- Don't rely on specific data existing unless it's seeded

### 5. Responsive Testing
- Test on multiple viewports
- Navigate first, then resize (to avoid losing session)

```typescript
test('should display correctly on mobile', async ({ page }) => {
  await examplePage.goto();  // Navigate first
  await examplePage.waitForLoad();
  
  await page.setViewportSize({ width: 375, height: 667 });  // Then resize
  await page.waitForTimeout(500);  // Allow reflow
  
  await expect(page.locator('[data-testid="title"]')).toBeVisible();
});
```

### 6. Error Handling
- Use `.catch(() => {})` for optional waits
- Handle rate limiting gracefully
- Skip tests when prerequisites aren't met

## Running Tests

### Local Development
```bash
# Run all tests
npx playwright test

# Run smoke tests only
npx playwright test --grep "@smoke"

# Run specific feature tests
npx playwright test tests/specs/properties/

# Run with UI mode for debugging
npx playwright test --ui
```

### CI/CD
```bash
# Smoke tests for quick validation
npx playwright test --grep "@smoke" --project=chromium

# Full regression suite
npx playwright test --grep "@regression" --project=chromium

# Production-safe tests
npx playwright test --grep "@prod" --project=chromium
```

## Common Patterns

### Conditional Test Execution
```typescript
test('should perform action', async () => {
  const count = await examplePage.getItemCount();
  if (count > 0) {
    // Proceed with test
  }
  // Test passes even if no items (not a failure condition)
});
```

### Dialog/Modal Handling
```typescript
async clickDeleteItem(): Promise<void> {
  await this.page.locator(this.deleteButton).click();
  await this.page.waitForSelector('.p-dialog, .p-confirmdialog', { 
    state: 'visible', 
    timeout: 5000 
  }).catch(() => {});
}

async confirmDelete(): Promise<void> {
  const confirmBtn = this.page.locator(
    '.p-dialog button:has-text("Yes"), button:has-text("Confirm")'
  ).first();
  await confirmBtn.click();
}
```

### Performance Testing
```typescript
test('should load within acceptable time', async () => {
  const startTime = Date.now();
  await examplePage.goto();
  await examplePage.waitForLoad();
  const loadTime = Date.now() - startTime;
  expect(loadTime).toBeLessThan(10000);  // 10 seconds max
});
```

## Troubleshooting

### Rate Limiting
The Auth API has rate limiting. If tests fail with 429 errors:
1. Add delays between test runs
2. Use `--workers=1` for sequential execution
3. Check `checkDemoUserAvailable` in test fixtures

### Session Issues
If authentication fails intermittently:
1. Ensure login completes before navigation
2. Check for localStorage/cookie persistence
3. Verify demo users are seeded in database

### Selector Not Found
1. Verify the element exists in DOM (inspect in browser)
2. Check for dynamic loading (add wait)
3. Verify data-testid matches current UI
4. Use multiple selector fallbacks

## Adding New Tests

### Checklist
1. [ ] Create Page Object Model in `tests/pages/`
2. [ ] Create test spec in appropriate `tests/specs/` subdirectory
3. [ ] Add appropriate tags (@smoke, @regression, @prod/@local)
4. [ ] Include page display tests
5. [ ] Include functionality tests
6. [ ] Include responsive tests
7. [ ] Include performance test
8. [ ] Test locally before committing
9. [ ] Update this documentation if needed

## Maintenance

### When UI Changes
1. Update affected Page Object Models
2. Update selectors to match new structure
3. Run affected tests to verify
4. Update this documentation if patterns change

### When Adding New Features
1. Add data-testid attributes to new UI elements
2. Create new Page Object Model
3. Create comprehensive test suite
4. Add appropriate tags for CI/CD
